textAnnotations.description:
The one or two horse power
ginwas found overgrown with
nettles completely seized
and rusted up. It was stripped
and painted and had a new
shaft fitted. It is believed to be
about 200 years old. Horse
gins were a common source
of power in the 18 and 19th
century being used in mines
mills and factories where no
water power was available
and before the steam engine
was invented. Some larger
ones were driven by up to 12
horses producing enormous
power.
